Policy.acknowledgement_statement: DNA and phenotypes were collected in studies supported by National Institutes of Health grants U01DE017018, P01NS045685 and R01DE016558. Additional resources were provided by the participating institutions: Battelle Memorial Institute; University at Buffalo; University of Florida; University of Maryland; University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. Genotyping was supported by the National Institute of Dental and Craniofacial Research, NIH, and performed at the Johns Hopkins Center for Inherited Disease Research under contract HHSN268201200008I; the University of Washington and National Center for Biotechnology Information, NIH, provided genotype-cleaning services.
Policy.ic_specific_access_term: These data may be used to study biological, psychological, and genetic factors related to Temporomandibular Joint Disorder (TMJD) and associated conditions.
